<HL>
   Tyco Completes Assets Purchase
</HL>
<DATE>
08/03/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), NO PAGE CITATION
</SO>
<CO>
   TYC A.WOI
</CO>
<IN>
TENDER OFFERS, MERGERS, ACQUISITIONS (TNM)
</IN>
<LP>
   EXETER, N.H. -- Tyco Laboratories Inc., a maker of fire
protection systems, packaging materials and electrical parts,
said it completed the acquisition of the operating assets of
Wormald International Ltd., a fire protection and
distribution company based in Australia.
   The transaction, which included $350 million in cash and
stock, had a total indicated value of more than $600 million.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   As a result of the acquisition, Tyco said it expects to
have sales of about $3.4 billion in its current fiscal year,
being adjusted to end June 30 to coordinate financial
reporting between Tyco and Wormald. In the year ended May 31,
Tyco had sales of $2.1 billion.
