   Flight International Group Inc.
</HL>
<DATE>
08/03/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), NO PAGE CITATION
</SO>
<CO>
   FLTIE WNEWS
</CO>
<LP>
   FLIGHT INTERNATIONAL GROUP Inc. (Newport News, Va.) --
Arthur R. Mann, 59 years old, was named chief operating
officer, executive vice president and a director of this
aviation services company. Mr. Mann succeeds Michael J.
Garrihy, 52, formerly president, chief operating officer and
a director of Flight, who has assumed the post of chairman
and chief executive officer of Jet Express Inc., a regional
air passenger carrier based in Newport News. Flight has an
option to purchase Jet before June 27, 1991. As part of the
restructuring, J. Nelson Happy, 46, chairman and chief
executive officer of Flight, was named president of Flight.
</LP>
