<HL>
   Canadian Steel Ingot Output
</HL>
<DATE>
08/03/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), NO PAGE CITATION
</SO>
<CO>
   CANDA
</CO>
<IN>
STEEL MANUFACTURERS (STL)
</IN>
<LP>
   OTTAWA -- Canadian steel ingot production totaled 254,057
metric tons in the week ended Saturday, down 3.2% from
262,440 the preceding week and 12% from 287,931 a year
earlier, Statistics Canada, a federal agency, said. A metric
ton is equal to about 2,204.6 pounds.
   For this year through Saturday, output totaled 8,261,581
metric tons, down 9.9% from 9,169,147 a year earlier.
</LP>
