<LP>
   EQUITABLE LIFE ASSURANCE SOCIETY OF THE U.S. (New York) --
Moody's Investors Service Inc. said it lowered its rating on
this insurer's financial strength to single-A-1 from
double-A-3. The rating concern also said it downgraded the
Euronote issue of the Equitable Life Financing Corp.
subsidiary to single-A-1 from double-A- 3. Moody's confirmed
its prime-1 rating on Equitable commercial paper. It cited
concerns about Equitable's "above average" exposure to highly
leveraged transactions and to the weakened commercial real
estate markets.
   ---
</LP>
<TEXT>
   TEXAS-NEW MEXICO POWER CO. -- Moody's Investors Service
Inc. said it lowered the ratings on about $190 million of
this Fort Worth, Texas, utility's first mortgage bonds, to
Baa-1 from single-A-3. The company is a unit of TNP
Enterprises Inc. Moody's said it believes the utility will be
subject to, among other things, continuing regulatory and
capital market risks and soaring costs, including
construction costs, for an extended period under which it
will also be under financial pressure. No official of the
company could be reached for comment.
</TEXT>
