<HL>
   Business Brief -- Havas S.A.:
   French Company's Revenue
   Climbed 28% in First Half
</HL>
<DATE>
08/03/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE B3C
</SO>
<CO>
   F.HAV
</CO>
<IN>
EARNINGS (ERN)
</IN>
<LP>
   French media and tourism group Havas S.A. said
consolidated revenue grew 28% in the first half to 11.76
billion francs ($2.21 billion) from 9.15 billion francs in
the year-earlier period.
   On a comparable structural and exchange-rate basis, Havas
said first-half revenue rose 18%. The company noted that
sales of SCAC Voyages S.A., acquired from Bollore
Technologies S.A. as part of an asset swap, have been
consolidated into the balance sheet starting April 1, 1990.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   A breakdown of Havas's revenue in the January-through-June
period showed tourism revenue up 44%, outdoor advertising
revenue up 20% and revenue from publishing and print media
also up 20%.
   Havas said sales outside of France accounted for 20% of
total sales in the half, up from 14% in the like period of
1989.
</TEXT>
