<HL>
   Business Brief -- Mesa Limited Partnership:
   Concern Reports Net Loss
   Widened in Second Quarter
</HL>
<DATE>
08/03/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), NO PAGE CITATION
</SO>
<CO>
   MLP
</CO>
<IN>
EARNINGS (ERN)
OIL, SECONDARY (OIS)
PETROLEUM (PET)
</IN>
<LP>
   Mesa Limited Partnership, Dallas, citing disappointing
prices for natural gas, said its net loss widened in the
second quarter to $50 million, or 49 cents a unit, from $13.4
million, or one cent a unit, a year earlier.
   T. Boone Pickens, the company's general partner, said Mesa
expects a 1990 average gas price of $1.60 per 1,000 cubic
feet this year. In the latest quarter, prices fell to $1.39
per 1,000 cubic feet from $1.56 a year earlier.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   Revenue fell to $62.3 million from $83.3 million.
   For the first half, Mesa reported a net loss of $68.2
million, or 79 cents a unit, on revenue of $158.8 million,
against profit of $1.2 million, or 14 cents a unit, on
revenue of $188.4 million, a year earlier.
   In the half, cash provided by operating activities
declined to $23.7 million from $62 million.
</TEXT>
